  "instructions": [
    "Trim and cut 200g green beans into 2cm pieces.",
    "In a saucepan, heat 1 tsp oil and sauté 1 minced garlic and 5g ginger until fragrant.",
    "Add 500ml vegetable stock, 10g kelp, 30ml soy sauce, 15ml yuzu juice, and 1g salt; bring to a simmer.",
    "Stir in 2g agar-agar until fully dissolved and let the broth simmer for 10 minutes.",
    "Add the prepared green beans to the broth and simmer for an additional 4 minutes until tender.",
    "Remove kelp, strain the liquid, and let the broth cool to 40°C while stirring.",
    "Whisk in 1 egg yolk until fully incorporated, then pour the mixture into a shallow dish.",
    "Chill the dish in the refrigerator for 30 minutes until it sets into a glassy gelatinous form."
  ],
